physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The patient had more than 300 smooth, dome-shaped, white to skin-colored 2- to 4-mm papules distributed over her face, neck, and upper trunk. Skin tags were seen on her axillae and eyelids. Smooth papules were present on her buccal mucosa and gingiva.

CT scans of the abdomen and pelvis revealed 3 tumors on her right kidney, which were treated with surgical enucleation. Gross examination revealed 3 pink to tan-colored nodules measuring 1.2 cm x 1.0 cm, 1.0 cm x 0.9 cm, and 2.5 cm x 2.0 cm. Histologic examination showed oncocytic renal neoplasms.
